The test failure for testDetermineCache() is quite annoying. Thanks [~lichangleo] for working on it and [~jlowe] for reviewing it. 
v4 patch looks good in overall except one place:
{code}
+  private static final Path TEST_ROOT_DIR =
+      new Path(System.getProperty("test.build.data", "/tmp"));
{code}
We should replace "/tmp" with System.getProperty("java.io.tmpdir") for tests to run smoothly in platform other than Linux.

The root directory should be the parent rather than a new parent, that way we're not scribbling random files in a directory shared by other things and other tests.  TEST_ROOT_DIR should be something like this:
{code}
  private static final Path TEST_ROOT_DIR = new Path(
      System.getProperty("test.build.data",
          System.getProperty("java.io.tmpdir")),
      TestClientDistributedCacheManager.class.getSimpleName());
{code}

And then the tearDown function can simply call FileUtil.fullyDelete(TEST_ROOT_DIR) rather than cleaning up individual files and having to maintain the list of potential things that could be leaked there.
